        <h3> Web Masters </h3>
          <p> So you want to be one of our Web Masters? You are in luck, because it is not that hard, and will get you introduced to web development. Mr. Bastoni has already trusted you with the username and password for webmaster access to the website (you need it to get to the Documentation). </p>
          <h4> Your Toolbox </h4>
            <p> You have some tools at your disposal when administering this website. </p>
            <ul>
              <li> You have a nice interface at <a href="/manage/">/manage/</a>. This is your greatest gift from the developers. Thank them for it. </li>
              <li> You can use the whole internet to help you write HTML or anything else you don't know. Thank Tim Berners Lee for this. </li>
              <li> The Web Developer. He or she may not be around, or we might not have one (they are kinda rare). Use them when you can, and they should be happy to help. They appreciate Thank You's.</li>
            </ul>
          <h4> The Big Rule </h4>
            <p><b><u><i> Make sure that nothing on this website will embarrass our sponsors. </i></u></b></p>
            <p> You've been trusted with a website. Don't mess up. </p>
          <h4> /manage/ </h4>
            <p> /manage/ is going to be where you do most of the things that you do. It is located at <a href="http://pnta.org/manage/">http://pnta.org/manage/</a>, and is relatively intuitive.</p>
            <p> It is used like any other website, having forms that you can fill out and submit. I'm going to go into detail on each of the pages.</p>
            <h5> News </h5>
              <p> News is quite simply the website news. I'm assuming that you can figure it out after playing with it for 3 minutes. Be aware there is no undo for the delete button.</p>
            <h5> Contact Information </h5>
              <p> Put in anyone who might need to be contacted for management of the website in here. That includes Mr. Bastoni and any Web Developers and any (dedicated) Web Masters.</p>
              <p> This is public information </p>
            <h5> Team Member Information </h5>
              <p> This is a database of the team, for record-keeping purposes.</p>
              <p> The flow of data for this is as follows: </p>
              <ol>
                <li> A person signs themselves up at <a class="noprintlink" href="http://pnta.org/join.php">http://pnta.org/join.php</a> </li>
                <li> When they hit submit, they are added to the database as "Unverified" </li>
                <li> A Web Master must come along and verify that they are actually part of the team, and not some random spambot. (by clicking the verify button) </li>
                <li> They are then moved to the Verified group and can be used for emails and database lookups later. </li>
              </ol>
              <p> This is <i>not</i> public information.</p>
            <h5> Team Member Viewer </h5>
              <p> This is a little something that I threw together to make it easy to use the data we collected in the Team Database. </p>
              <p> The top box is used to filter the results. You are given words on the buttons that you can combine to create sentences such as, "Match Only The Records Where The YOG Is Less Than '2013' AND The Type Is 'Student'".</p>
              <p> In order to create words that have arbitrary values, like '2013' or 'Student', use the button labeled "Click Here To Enter A Value". </p>
              <p> You can send emails to the people who match your filter in the form below. </p>
            <h5> Resources </h5>
              <p> Resources could also be called "links" or something similar. Its pretty self explanatory. </p>
            <h5> Sponsors </h5>
              <p> Sponsors are very important. They give us money so that we can do awesome stuff and they need our respect. Make sure that after a database reset, our sponsors are still there. If you ever lose the sponsor data, <a onclick="document.getElementById('samplesponsortable').style.display = 'block';" href="#samplesponsortable">click here</a>. Start with that list, and ask Mr. Bastoni if there have been any additions since my time.</p>
