            <h5> Files </h5>
              <p> This is here for Mr. Bastoni. Let it be. </p>
            <h5> Images </h5>
              <p> We also have a team photo album! You can upload pictures under "File Upload" (Chose the right settings), and they will be automatically added to the photo album. </p>
              <p> You can also have the non-web-master team members upload pictures at <a href="http://pnta.org/pictures.php">http://pnta.org/pictures.php</a>. You then need to verify the pictures on the "Manage Uploaded Pictures" page.
          <h4> Backups </h4>
            <p> Every September somebody should create a backup of this website. If there are no web developers, a web master must do it. <a href="/documentation/devel.php#backup">Instructions are here.</a></p>
          <h4> Email accounts </h4>
            <p> I think you deserve a pnta.org email account, so ask Mr. Bastoni or a web developer to set one up for you. </p>
          <h4> Closing Remarks </h4>
            <p> Thanks for taking the time to read this. You can manage this website now! If you need help try to find it in this order:
            <ol>
              <li> Use the internet. Google is your friend. (Unless its a specific problem with our website... Google won't have a clue. [Or at-least it doesn't in 2013, I don't know what Google can do now!]) </li>
              <li> Use your fellow web masters. They are probably pretty nice (just look at them first, are they having a bad day?) </li>
              <li> Ask the Web Developers. (Keep in mind that sometimes we don't have any). You should go to them if its a problem with the website giving you an error. </li>
              <li> Ask Mr. Bastoni. He's a smart guy. His email should be <b>mbastoni@pnta.org</b>. Don't go to him for just anything though... He's a busy guy. </li>
              <li> If all else fails you can email me. I'm Kevin Johnson and I will graduate (or maybe graduated) in 2015. I designed the current revision of this website (assuming that the Web Developers don't keep my name on here if they throw out the code...).
              I'm looking to go into a career into Web Development, so I know my stuff. You can email me at <b>kevin@coolkev.com</b>. I promise to be nice!!! </li>
            </ol>
        
